robert nardelli  wikipedia robert nardelli from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this biography of a living person needs additional citations for verification please help by adding reliable sources contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced must be removed immediately especially if potentially libelous or harmful july  learn how and when to remove this template message bob nardelli being introduced by general cartwright robert louis bob nardelli born may   in old forge pennsylvania is an american businessman he was the chairman and chief executive officer of chrysler he had earlier served in a similar capacity at the home depot from december  to january  prior to that nardelli had risen to become one of the top four executives at general electric condé nast portfolio named nardelli as one of the worst american ceos of all time he attended rockford auburn high school in rockford illinois and received his bachelor of science in business from western illinois university in macomb where he was a member of the tau kappa epsilon fraternity nardelli also earned an mba from the university of louisville he is married to susan l schmulbach with four children and attends roman catholic church contents  general electric  home depot  cocacola  chrysler  freedom group  references general electricedit he joined general electric in  as an entrylevel manufacturing engineer from  to  nardelli was an executive for a division of the construction equipment maker j i case company which was then part of tenneco by  he had risen to president and ceo of ge power systems also having the title of ge senior vice president nardelli was often known as little jack after his mentor jack welch whom nardelli had ambitions to succeed as ceo of ge when jack welch retired as chairman and ceo of ge a lengthy and wellpublicized succession planning saga ensued nardelli competed with james mcnerney and jeffrey r immelt to succeed welch with immelt winning the threeway race nardelli and mcnerney left ge as was welchs plan about  minutes after welch let him go nardelli received a job offer from kenneth langone who at the time was on the boards of both ge and the home depot home depotedit nardelli became ceo of home depot in december  despite having no retail experience using the six sigma management strategy used at ge he dramatically overhauled the company and replaced its entrepreneurial culture of innovative product design with one focused on relentless costcutting he changed the decentralized management structure by eliminating and consolidating division executives he also installed processes and streamlined operations most notably implementing a computerized automated inventory system and centralizing supply orders at the atlanta headquarters his stint is widely noted to be the most repulsive in the history of home depot nardellis toxic actions served to kill an enduring company culture and turned home depot into a laggard nardelli was credited with doubling the sales of the chain and improving its competitive position revenue increased from  billion in  to  billion in  while net earnings after tax rose from  billion to  billion during nardellis tenure home depot stock was essentially steady while competitor lowes stock doubled which along with his  million compensation eventually earned the ire of investors his blunt critical and autocratic management style turned off employees and the public nardelli was notably criticized for cutting back on knowledgeable fulltime employees with experience in the trades and replacing them with parttime help with little relevant experience this move reduced costs but hurt customer service at a time when lowes was making inroads nationwide while the board strongly stood by him for most of his tenure questions about his leadership mounted in  and in an ominous portent of the near future he was the only director present at the annual meeting at that meeting he only allowed shareholders to speak for one minute each when the board reportedly ousted him in january  nardellis severance package was estimated at  million he was succeeded by the home depot vice chairman and executive vice president frank blake blake had served as nardellis deputy at both ge power systems and home depot during his tenure at home depot nardelli met president george w bush at the white house in  and was appointed to bushs council on service and civic participation although he is no longer a member nardelli also hosted a garden receptionfundraiser for bush at his atlanta home on may   cocacolaedit while ceo of home depot nardelli was also briefly on the board of directors for cocacola starting in  chrysleredit on august   he became chairman and ceo of chrysler which had recently been taken private by private equity firm cerberus capital management his annual salary at chrysler was  with other compensation not publicly disclosed its rumored that the terms were that he wouldnt be paid unless chrysler succeeded if they did succeed he would be paid a salary along the lines of  million on february   before his first daytona  race as chrysler ceo nardelli guaranteed that dodge would win the race for the first time since  and that he would award a  million bonus to the dodge team that did it ryan newman the driver of the  alltel dodge fulfilled this promise and his car owner roger penske collected the  million bounty on december   in an appearance on cnns situation room with wolf blitzer nardelli was asked so what do you say about the argument that the japanese the germans koreans make better cars than the americans he responded we spent about half a billion dollars in the first several months our warranty costs are down  its an interesting comparison because in the hearing today going around the panel the majority of the senators said that citing specific vehicles that they own that theyve got    miles the comment was you guys are making them too good and therefore were not buying vehicles and were contributing to your problem that was from the senators on the committee today on march   nardelli said that chrysler financial would require a second round of loans on april   it was alleged by an unnamed federal watchdog agency that a  million loan from the government was turned down on the grounds that it would have required that executive compensation be capped according to contemporary media coverage as part of the economic stimulus package congress approved compensation limits and the treasury is working on clarifying what the firms must do to comply with the rules in other words the executives were asked to sign the waivers without knowing what specific limits the treasury might set  on april   chrysler filed for chapter  bankruptcy the same day nardelli announced that he would leave the company as soon as the bankruptcy was over and his replacement was announced sergio marchionne  who would likely face a pay cap freedom groupedit robert nardelli became ceo of the freedom group in september  as the north carolinabased gun maker searched for a permanent ceo in march  he stepped down as ceo of the freedom group and as the head of the operations and advisory business of cerberus capital management lp referencesedit  portfolios worst american ceos of all time cnbccom  retrieved    robert l nardelli nndbcom retrieved    flaherty joseph  december  how home depot copied apple to build an ingenious new bucket wiredcom condé nast retrieved  september  in  marcus retired and brought on bob nardelli as ceo nardelli had been one of jack welchs hatchet men at ge and he spent the next seven years driving down costs—at the expense of home depots reputation for innovationmarcus forced nardelli out in  and brought in a home depot veteran to right the ship by returning the focus to developing and selling innovative products exclusive to home depot   nardellis downfall its all about the stock archived january   at the wayback machine  lublin joann s zimmerman ann terhune chad january   behind nardellis abrupt exit the wall street journal   joe nocera the board wore chicken suits new york times  may   vlasic bill robert nardelli  the new york times topicsnytimescom retrieved    nardellibush article that mentions presidential council archived may   at the wayback machine  paul harris article that mentions bush nardelli garden reception observerguardiancouk retrieved    financial times story about nardellis salary  httpswebarchiveorgwebhttpsportsyahoocomnascarnewsslugapnascardaytonaprovaptypelgns archived from the original on february   retrieved september    missing or empty title help   cnn nardelli inverview transcriptscnncom retrieved    greg gardner free press business writer  nardelli says chrysler financial needs second round of loans detroit free press freepcom retrieved    pay rule led chrysler to spurn loan washington post washingtonpostcom retrieved    marchionne confirmed as postch chrysler ceo autoblogcom retrieved    next chrysler ceo faces pay cap detroit free press freepcom  retrieved    cerberuss freedom group withdraws plans for ipo bloomberg retrieved  april    nardelli steps down from most of his cerberus roles dealbook retrieved  march   usa today qa during home depot days alic margaret robert l nardelli – business biographies reference for business  grow brian january   out at home depot behind the flameout of controversial ceo bob nardelli msnbc business week  mui ylan q january   seeing red over a golden parachute home depots ceo resigns and his hefty payout raises ire washington post p d  nardeli bob august  chryslers secret weapon military talent gi jobs interview transcript interview with joshua hudson  speakers robert nardelli  chairman president and ceo the home depot inc chief executive series new york university stern school of business november    profile with links to transcript and video of his interview the best  worst managers of   best manager robert nardelli  home depot b